HEADWORD: Aguardiente
<hw>A`guar*di*en"te</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.,
contr. of <ets>agua ardiente</ets> burning water (L. <ets>aqua</ets>
water + <ets>ardens</ets> burning).]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A inferior
brandy of Spain and Portugal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A strong alcoholic drink, especially pulque.</def>
<mark>[Mexico and Spanish America.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

